Remarks

This interface is a top of inheritance tree of interfaces which declares their inputs. Supporting this interface means that unit does not require any input data Usually this interface is used in child units creation (usually this is for indicators), to limit the types of possible parent units. For example, if your indicator does not require input data, then any other indicator can create it inside itself. But if your indicator needs ISeries<T> then only IScriptUnitOnSeries can create it and use, because they can provide input data for your indicator
